Fans of American musician T.I might have waited a long time to see their favourite rapper on Mzansi soil but they will be delighted to learn that the wait is over. The 37-year old will be performing in Rosebank tonight in what will be a short visit to the country. T.I, real name Clifford Joseph Harris Jr took to social media to announce that he will be setting the city of gold, Johannesburg, alight this Thursday, much to the delight of many of his fans on the internet. “SOUTH AFRICA!! I’m heading your way!! Meet me at Sumo Night Club this THURSDAY #Johannesburg TURN IT!!,” he announced on Twitter.  